@node "intro" "Introduction to AmiTarot"
            @{b}What is this program?@{ub}


   AmiTarot is a program that shows you the answers to your questions
by using a random generator based on the exact moment you "press any key
to continue."  So, in essence, your subconscious determines the layout
(just like shuffling with a real deck).


I only have 2 basic Tarot cards layouts at the moment.  But there are
@{"plans" link "futur"} for more in the future.


It can be controlled by either the @{"keyboard" link "howto"} or the mouse now.

@endnode
@node "requi" "What do I need for this?"

           @{b}Requirements@{ub}

   - Amiga computer (is there really any other? (c;  )

   - OS2.1 or higher

   - textfield.gadget (Aminet search for "textfield.lha") *NEW*




