@node "histo" "What have I already done with AmiTarot?"

    @{b}Version History:@{ub}

v1.66

   - Added button gadgets for the layout selection.

   - Made the background color for the different windows.  Hopefully

     it will be able to be set by the user soon.



v1.63

   Fixed Bugs:

   - The text field in the card window wasn't able to keep the text

     within the borders.  This has been fixed by using textfield.gadget

     The only drawback is that you now have to have textfield.gadget

     in your system.  


   - Added Gadgets for the card title and the position of the card.


   - There are no Enforcer hits when I run it on my system.


v1.60

   Fixed Bugs:

   - If the main window somehow got in front of the card window, the

     card window was stuck back there until you brought it forward or 

     closed that window.  Now you can click anywhere in the main window

     and the card window will pop back in front of the main window, and 
    
     it will be centered on the main window again.


   - The intro animation text disappeared before it left the window, 

     making it a little odd to watch.  That problem has been fixed and 

     the intro animation has been sped up by 2x, so the animations are

     faster... making them a little less annoying  (c;  (hmmm maybe that 
    
     can be a shareware thing later)

   
   - The text in the card window wasn't formatted very well... I added 

    a routine that formats the text a little better.  Hopefully it is 

    truly font sensitive (I've tried it with a few different fonts with 
    
    good results.)

    

     Thanks to Petr Cisar for reporting these.  (c:


v1.52

   - Added the abilit to click and speed past the animation of the title (the one that repeats)


v1.51

   - Added full tooltype support for the screenmode tooltype.  Options are "select" "best" and "workbench"


v1.50

   - This was a fairly major update as far as the code went, mouse support is now fully functional

   - other minor code cleanups


v1.15

   - The card window is now centered on the main window

   - minor and major code cleanups



v1.11

   - Changed GUI to only be one main window (graphic) and the card window

   - You can now close the main window to quit the program at any point.

   - Added the AmiTarot.guide documentation.



v1.10

   - Font is now controlled by the program instead of being at the mercy

      of your system font (which may be too big for the display)


   fixed bugs:

      - removed enforcer hit when pressing any key for the cards to be

         dealt (thanks to Petr Cisar for reminding me this was happening)


      - system fonts that were too big didn't show up well in the display

         (thanks again to Petr Cisar for pointing this one out)



   known bugs:


      - still the thing with the mouse... I'm trying to decide a good

         way to deal with this one.... maybe each card is a gadget... (c;


v1.02:


   - now gives choice to open on workbench screen at start of program

   - allows user to end credits with a keypress  (Chryse reminded me)



   fixed bugs:


      - cardwindow opening in low memory situation, bug was a result

         of opening on workbench, not low memory.  if the memory is

         actually too low to open the card window, the program still

         terminates (by design, not bug)



   known bugs:


      - if you try to use the mouse and make the wrong window

         active, the program doesn't receive your input.

         (be sure that if you can't give input that you select

            the smaller of the 2 main windows)



v1.00/1.01:


   - Initial release

   - basic vector graphics

   - opens own screen unless low memory, then opens on workbench

   - enforcer hit when pressing any key to lay cards out



   Known Bugs:


      - if there is a low memory situation, the window with the

         card description doesn't open.  To avoid a crash, I

         end the program on any error like that.


      - if you try to use the mouse and make the wrong window

         active, the program doesn't receive your input.

         (be sure that if you can't give input that you select

            the smaller of the 2 main windows)



Please send any bug reports to vancel@flash.net with the following
information:


   your computer model

   your OS version

   brief description of what happened


thanks  (c:

@endnode
